PORT=3000
No setup required. Just keep it as 3000 (or your preferred port).

CLOUDINARY SETUP
Step 1: Go to https://cloudinary.com
Step 2: Create a free account and verify your email
Step 3: After login, go to Dashboard
You will see:
Cloud Name
API Key
API Secret
Copy them and add to your .env:
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret
CLOUDINARY_URL format:
CLOUDINARY_URL=cloudinary://API_KEY:API_SECRET@CLOUD_NAME
Example:
CLOUDINARY_URL=cloudinary://123456789:abcdef@mycloud

CLERK SETUP
Step 1: Go to https://clerk.com
Step 2: Sign up
Step 3: Create a new application
After creating app:
Go to → API Keys section
You will get:
Publishable Key
Secret Key
Add to .env:
CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_publishable_key
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
For Webhook:
Step 4: Go to Webhooks section
Step 5: Create Endpoint
Step 6: Add your backend webhook URL (example: https://yourbackend.com/api/webhook)
Step 7: After creating webhook, copy Signing Secret
Add:
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=your_webhook_secret

GOOGLE CLOUD API KEY
Step 1: Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
Step 2: Create new project
Step 3: Go to "APIs & Services" → Credentials
Step 4: Click "Create Credentials" → API Key
Step 5: Copy generated API key
Add:
GOOGLE_CLOUD_API_KEY=your_google_api_key
(Optional but recommended: restrict key usage under "API restrictions")
DATABASE_URL (Neon PostgreSQL)

Since you're using Neon:
Step 1: Go to https://neon.tech
Step 2: Login
Step 3: Create a new project
Step 4: Choose PostgreSQL version
Step 5: After project creation, go to Dashboard
Click “Connection Details”
You will see a connection string like:
postgresql://username:password@ep-xyz.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require
Copy the full string and add:
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@ep-xyz.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require
Important:
Always keep sslmode=require
Never commit this file to GitHub
Add .env to .gitignore


Your final .env will look like:

PORT=3000
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=
CLOUDINARY_URL=
CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=
GOOGLE_CLOUD_API_KEY=
DATABASE_URL=


#Live Clerk keys.(Production mode)After creating Clerk Production Instance.
#CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#CLERK_SECRET_KEY=